<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/96184137-jim"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1555542936i/96184137._UX100_CR0,14,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/96184137-jim">Jim</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Unequivocally yes. It will forever change anyone’s opinion that graphic novels are a “kids thing” or “nerds”. <br/>The story may be told primarily in pictu<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Unequivocally yes. It will forever change anyone’s opinion that graphic novels are a “kids thing” or “nerds”. <br />The story may be told primarily in pictures, but they illustrate a rich, powerful true story of a father and his son, who learns what his father’s unbelievable struggle in a dark time in history affected not only him, but his own life as well decades later. The animal symbolism is parallel to that of Animal Farm, but far more lucrative in using art and words to do so.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
