<span id="freeTextContainer2221567404005871158">When I was a kid I read comic books (mostly Superman). The Maus books are the only graphic novels I&apos;ve read and I consider them masterpieces (Mausterpieces?). Like Spiegelman&apos;s alter ego, I was a middle class child growing up in Queens (NYC), the son of Holocaust survivors and couldn&apos;t communicate with my father when I was growing up. He got it down perfectly. It was spot on and ranks among the best of Holocaust related literature.</span>
  <span id="freeText2221567404005871158" style="display:none">When I was a kid I read comic books (mostly Superman). The Maus books are the only graphic novels I've read and I consider them masterpieces (Mausterpieces?). Like Spiegelman's alter ego, I was a middle class child growing up in Queens (NYC), the son of Holocaust survivors and couldn't communicate with my father when I was growing up. He got it down perfectly. It was spot on and ranks among the best of Holocaust related literature.</span>
